<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus Gessneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="Gessneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus Gessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[sic!] 
<normalizedToken originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
, 1880: 273. Sex not given. Syntypes. Type locality: Switzerland. Lectotype ♀ hereby designated, labelled: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Suisse”">&quot;Suisse&quot;</normalizedToken>
, &quot;DEI GISHym 89367&quot; [printed], &quot;coll. Desbrochers [handwritten] k. [kollektsija = coll.] A. Jakovleva [nomin. A. Jakovlev]&quot; [printed], &quot;SYNTYPUS [printed in red] 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus gessneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gessneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus gessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="ANDRÉ">ANDRE</normalizedToken>
, 1880 [handwritten] teste A. Taeger 20[printed]18 [handwritten]&quot; [white with a red frame]. &quot;Lectotype 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus gessneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gessneri">Dolerus gessneri</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, E" journalOrPublisher="Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B2" refString="Andre, E, 1880. Species des Hymenopteres d'Europe &amp; d'Algerie. L'Auteur, Beaune (Cote-d'Or), 1[1879-1882](7): 237-300. [catalogue 29-36]" title="Species des Hymenopteres d'Europe &amp; d'Algerie. L'Auteur, Beaune (Cote-d'Or), 1 [1879 - 1882] (7): 237 - 300. [catalogue 29 - 36]" year="1880">
<normalizedToken originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
1880
</bibRefCitation>
vide A. Taeger 2022 des.&quot; [red, printed]. Good condition, but slightly dusty. Paralectotypes: 2♂ (one without flagella) with the same data (except 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“♂”">&quot;♂&quot;</normalizedToken>
[printed], &quot;DEI-GISHym 89365&quot; and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“D…">&quot;D...</normalizedToken>
89366&quot; and &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="Paralectotypus" lsidName="Paralectotypus" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="genus">Paralectotypus</taxonomicName>
&quot; instead of &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="Lectotypus" lsidName="Lectotypus" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="genus">Lectotypus</taxonomicName>
&quot;). All in ZIN.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The color form of 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus gessneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gessneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus gessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a red-banded abdomen was described as a distinct species, 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. labiosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="labiosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. labiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Konow, 1897 (
<bibRefCitation author="Konow, FW" journalOrPublisher="Wiener entomologische Zeitung," pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="173 - 187" refId="B95" refString="Konow, FW, 1897b. Neue palaearctische Tenthrediniden. Wiener entomologische Zeitung, 16 (6): 173 - 187" title="Neue palaearctische Tenthrediniden." volume="16" year="1897 b">Konow 1897b</bibRefCitation>
), but was later mostly treated as a synonym (sometimes also as a subspecies) of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. gessneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="gessneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. gessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because intermediate color forms with variable red markings on the abdomen occur. The specimens from the Russian Far East with completely black forelegs, which have sometimes been determined as 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. gessneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="gessneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. gessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, probably belong to some other 
<taxonomicName authority=")" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus (Equidolerus) subsp. subgen." order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" species="gessneri" subGenus="Equidolerus" subSpecies="subgen.">Dolerus (subgen. Equidolerus)</taxonomicName>
species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus gessneri" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gessneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus gessneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a Holarctic species, needs a revision, because COI barcoding data suggest that it could include more than one species, and some morphological characters correlate with the genetic data. There are three BIN clusters (BOLD:AAL2317, BOLD:ACE7304, BOLD:ACE3617) diverging by 1.8-2.3%. BOLD:AAL2317 is closest to 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. timidus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="timidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. timidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and BOLD:ACE7304 is closest to 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. pratensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="pratensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(minimum divergence in both cases 1.2%). All three BIN clusters are represented in Fennoscandia, two of which (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Dolerus gessneri (Andre, 1880) (ZMUO. 045118). A. Dorsal habitus; B. Lateral habitus. Dolerus sp. near gessneri (ZMUO. 045279); C. Dorsal habitus; D. Lateral habitus." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719530" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">19</figureCitation>
) have been found in Finland.
</paragraph>
